# Linux ISO
CTA uses Linux Mint (Mate) as a base distro for machines that can't run Windows or MacOS. This repo contains instructions and example files to create the custon ISO / installer.

## Basics
get vanilla
mount
add / customise:
- isolinux.cfg (tweak to include preseed file on boot)
- lta.preseed (specify user details, etc)
- /etc/skel (add shortcuts, PDFs to users desktops on user creation)
fix manifests / packages?
unmount